      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(providers): use native reasoning mode for Gemini instead of tagged",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nGemini 2.5 Pro/Flash exposes reasoning via native `thinkingParts` through `thinkingConfig.includeThoughts`. The `google-gemini` family hook in `GOOGLE_GEMINI_PROVIDER_HOOKS` was unconditionally returning `\"tagged\"`, which injects a `<think>…</think>/<final>…</final>` directive into the system prompt at the same time as the native thinking config is active.\n\nThe model then:\n1. Emits a native `thought:true` part\n2. Opens a `<think>` text block per the injected directive\n3. Pivots to a tool call before closing `</think>`\n4. Returns an empty post-tool assistant turn (`content: []`)\n\nGateway logs: `incomplete turn detected: stopReason=stop payloads=0` — surfacing a spurious error to the user, while burning ~140K input tokens.\n\n### Changes\n\n- **`extensions/google/provider-hooks.ts`** — override `resolveReasoningOutputMode` in `GOOGLE_GEMINI_PROVIDER_HOOKS` to return `\"native\"`, superseding the `google-gemini` family default of `\"tagged\"`\n- **`src/utils/provider-utils.ts`** — remove the now-dead `BUILTIN_REASONING_OUTPUT_MODES` entry keyed on `\"google-generative-ai\"`: all production callers pass the plugin id `\"google\"` (never the transport API string), so the map was unreachable; the plugin hook was always the effective path\n- Tests updated in both `provider-utils.test.ts` and `extensions/google/index.test.ts`\n\n## Verification\n\n**Real behavior proof**\n\n- `Behavior addressed`: Gemini 2.5 Pro/Flash with `thinkingDefault: medium` producing `payloads=0` errors and spurious user-facing error messages on turns that include a tool call, as reported in #69220\n- `Real environment tested`: macOS arm64, Node v24.15.0, local source checkout\n- `Exact steps or command run after this patch`: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/utils/provider-utils.test.ts` (25/25 passed); `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/google/index.test.ts` (8/8 passed); `node ./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check` (clean); `tsgo -p tsconfig.core.json` (exit 0)\n- `Evidence after fix`: `isReasoningTagProvider(\"google\", ...)` now returns `false`; the `<think>/<final>` system-prompt directive is no longer injected for Gemini; native `thinkingParts` are processed without conflict\n- `Observed result after fix`: all touched tests green, no format/lint/type errors\n- `What was not tested`: live Gemini 2.5 Pro/Flash end-to-end run confirming absence of `payloads=0` error (requires live API key + Crabbox); older Gemini models without native thinking (expected unaffected — `\"native\"` mode simply means core does not inject text-tag reasoning directives)\n\nFixes #69220",
        "branch": "fix/gemini-reasoning-output-mode",
